# Telegram Bot App

This project is a simple Telegram bot deployed on Heroku. The bot interacts with Telegram APIs and uses various environment variables for configuration. Follow the steps below to deploy it easily to your Heroku account.

## Deploy to Heroku

Click the button below to deploy this app directly to Heroku.

[![Deploy](https://www.herokucdn.com/deploy/button.svg)](https://heroku.com/deploy?template=https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name)

## Configuration

Before deploying, make sure to set the necessary environment variables for your app. You can do this through the Heroku dashboard or by using the `app.json` file which defines the required variables.

The following environment variables need to be set:

- **API_ID**: Obtain from [Telegram's Developer Portal](https://my.telegram.org).
- **API_HASH**: Obtain from [Telegram's Developer Portal](https://my.telegram.org).
- **BOT_TOKEN**: Get this from [@BotFather](https://t.me/botfather).
- **OWNER_ID**: Optional. The user ID of the bot owner.
- **PM_AUTH_USERS**: Optional. A list of user IDs with no time limits.
- **CHAT_ID**: Optional. The ID of the group chat.
- **DOWNLOAD_DIRECTORY**: Optional. Directory where files will be downloaded.
- **CRED_TEXT**: Optional. The credential text for your bot.

### Running Locally or vps

To run this app on your local machine or vps, follow these steps:

1. Clone the repo:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
   cd your-repo-name

Install the dependencies:


pip install -r requirements.txt
Set the required environment variables. You can do this by creating a .env file or exporting them in your terminal:

Example .env file:

API_ID=your_api_id
API_HASH=your_api_hash
BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token
OWNER_ID=your_owner_id
Run the app locally:

python app.py
